Squeeze the @Steamed Basmati Rice{1%pouch} pouch to separate the grains. Tear a stripe approx 2cm along the top.

Cook the rice according to pack instructions. Set aside until serving.

Meanwhile, cut the @Medium Tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Zest and halve the @Lime{1}. Roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all).

In a #medium bowl{}, add the tomato chunks, half the coriander and half the lime juice. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix to combine, then set aside your salsa.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Mayonnaise{32%g}, @Chipotle Paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water for the Mayo{1%tbsp}.

Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In another medium bowl, add the sliced baby gem, a squeeze of lime juice and drizzle of oil. Season with salt and pepper, toss to combine, then set aside both bowls.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In another medium bowl, add the @British Chicken Thighs{3}, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, and garlic. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Rub to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything's ready, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm slices.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir through the lime zest and remaining coriander, then share the zesty rice between your bowls.

Top with the baby gem salad, sliced chicken and tomato salsa. Drizzle over the chipotle mayo to finish.

Enjoy!